# Day 1 – Getting Back to Python

Today I started my DSA journey with Python. Before jumping into DSA, I wanted to refresh the Python basics that I'll be using throughout the journey.

## What I revised

* Lists
* Strings
* Dictionaries
* Sets
* Basic Time Complexity (Big O)

## Practice

### Lists

```python
num = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 32, 45, 322]

print(num[0])
print(num[-1])
print(len(num))
```

### Strings

```python
text = "datastructure"

print(len(text))
print(text[0])
print(text[-1])
```

### Dictionary

```python
student = {
    "name": "Nida",
    "branch": "CSE",
    "year": 3
}

print(student["name"])
print(student["branch"])
print(student["year"])
```

### Set

```python
num = [2, 4, 2, 6, 4, 8, 8, 10]

print(set(num))
```

## A few things I understood today

* Lists can be changed, but strings can't.
* Dictionaries make it easy to store related information using keys.
* Sets automatically remove duplicate values.
* A single loop that goes through every element has a time complexity of **O(n)**.

